programing methodology day 6

constructure (생성자)
public static class Cat {
		String name;
		int age;
		
		void tell_about_you() {
			System.out.printf("name is %s, age is : %d \n", name, age);
		}
		
		Cat(String n, int a) {
			name = n;
			age = a;
		}
	}

reference variable vs basic variable
reference : pointer
basic : just variable

class variable and class method
static field : shared to all instances, allocated at starting class
static method : can be called without creat object

access modifier (접근 제한자)
public : 어디서나 접근 허용.
(default) : 같은 패키지 내에서만.
protected : 같은 패키지 + 서브클래스.
private : 선언된 클래스 내부만.
